{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-1-chapter-level-1-tsx","path":"/topics/feverish-children-management/have-i-got-the-right-topic/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"d6888baa-d127-575e-8a84-9dc99c5a3fc7","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","depth":1,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field e4f86a3f-f9a6-49e1-89ce-22a8179714b5 --><h1>Have I got the right topic?</h1><!-- end field e4f86a3f-f9a6-49e1-89ce-22a8179714b5 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f78ec159-01d1-46c7-842c-6e5d1d6e69a1 --><!-- begin field 21c246c0-3efc-4375-b462-acbc01572b6e --><p>From age 1 month to 16 years.</p><!-- end field 21c246c0-3efc-4375-b462-acbc01572b6e --><!-- begin field 01a49711-0ea5-45bd-ac80-8d4f3d50fe3e --><p>This CKS topic is largely based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) clinical guideline <em>Feverish illness in children: assessment and initial management in children younger than 5 years </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-management/references/\">NICE, 2017</a>].</p><p>This CKS topic covers the management of infants and children aged 1 month to 16 years who have a feverish illness, including when and how to use antipyretic drug treatment and self-care advice for parents/carers.</p><p>This CKS topic does not cover the initial assessment of an infant or child with a feverish illness, or the diagnosis of other underlying causes of fever.</p><p>There are separate CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/analgesia-mild-to-moderate-pain/\">Analgesia - mild-to-moderate pain</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/febrile-seizure/\">Febrile seizure</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/\">Feverish children - risk assessment</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/nsaids-prescribing-issues/\">NSAIDs - prescribing issues</a>.</p><p>The target audience for this CKS topic is healthcare professionals working within the NHS in the UK, and providing first contact or primary healthcare.</p><!-- end field 01a49711-0ea5-45bd-ac80-8d4f3d50fe3e --><!-- end item f78ec159-01d1-46c7-842c-6e5d1d6e69a1 -->","topic":{"id":"57afe72a-44a7-59f4-8b36-6eb7a2a98627","topicId":"cad66ea8-fd1e-4e8e-8a0a-4373743b9757","topicName":"Feverish children - management","slug":"feverish-children-management","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2018","chapters":[{"id":"37563924-9b7f-5010-ac82-0a34cfebfade","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d6888baa-d127-575e-8a84-9dc99c5a3fc7","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cd28b465-db51-5aaa-a791-4edb2d2190b9","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"2d5e04dc-f0b0-5c21-8aa0-e3dae4707252","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"214e8c64-9ed6-54f9-80fc-05f388a4efad","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"bc5b7055-3b0e-5b8e-af94-087af7c8df52","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"8a12ce09-3e70-5d55-a94e-0bb219807058","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8fb8cc12-0b57-52bd-81a1-f665491b6461","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"e816954e-05aa-518b-9149-859f2eddaf82","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"80058d93-ee7d-5b6b-9999-cb059bb153ca","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"803d1dc1-882b-5b81-81e0-50f6ea2042a2","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"daec1f52-f8e3-5f92-9eeb-3f00896c0fc9","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"c06763f6-d0bc-5267-9afc-39f4d9ab0b23"